Q2: "What happens in your schema if an Admin deletes a Product that exists in someone's order history?"

This is a referential integrity question. OrderItem has a foreign key to Product. If you delete the product, the DB will throw a constraint violation — which is the correct default behavior, because you'd be destroying order history. The right solution is to add a isActive boolean to Product and do soft deletes — mark it inactive so it no longer appears in listings, but the row remains in the DB so OrderItem foreign keys stay valid.

